c: 4
v: 157
t: "and (due to) their saying, \"We killed Messiah, Isa the son of Maryam, messenger of Allah.\" And they did not kill him nor did they crucify him, but for them, he (the one crucified) was made to resemble (Isa), and those who differ in it are certainly in a doubt about it. They do not have any knowledge of it, they follow nothing but conjecture and they certainly did not kill him"